2 unit(s) Flatbread
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
100 g Bacon Strips
2 tbsp Caesar Dressing
28 g Croutons
113 g Mushrooms
½ cup Marinara Sauce
56 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add bacon. (NOTE: For 4 servings, cook bacon in batches.) Cook for 5-8 min, flipping occasionally, until crispy.**
Remove the pan from heat. Using tongs, transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined cutting board. Set aside. Discard all but 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) bacon fat.

Reheat the same pan with bacon fat over medium-high.
While the pan heats, cut mushrooms into 1/4-inch slices.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
When the pan is hot, add mushrooms and peppers. Cook for 5-6 min, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are softened and peppers are tender-crisp.
Remove from heat, then season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, on a parchment-lined baking sheet, arrange flatbreads. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets.)
Toast flatbreads in the bottom of the oven for 2-3 min, until softened. (NOTE: For 4 servings, toast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Spread half the marinara sauce over flatbreads and sprinkle cheese over top.
Top with mushroom-pepper mixture and half the bacon.
Bake assembled flatbreads in the middle of the oven for 7-8 min, until cheese is melted and flatbreads are browned and crisp. (NOTE: For 4 servings, bake flatbreads in the top and middle of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.) (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)

Meanwhile, to a large bowl, add croutons and spring mix. Drizzle with Caesar dressing, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine.

Cut flatbreads into quarters.
Divide flatbreads and salad between plates.
Top salad with remaining bacon.
Serve remaining marinara sauce on the side.